    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hangings attached to the front of or covering a lectern, often embroidered or painted, sometimes in the liturgical color corresponding to the current season of the church calendar.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079245/Catholic Encyclopedia [online] (2003-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kleed dat aan de voorkant van een lessenaar hangt of waarmee men de lessenaar bedekt, vaak voorzien van borduurwerk of beschilderd, soms in de liturgische kleur die hoort bij het betreffende seizoen van de kerkelijke kalender.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>掛於讀經臺前方或覆蓋其上的懸掛物，通常繡有或繪有圖樣，有些用色會與教會年曆上當季之禮拜儀式顏色一致。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
